AB  - Digital Twin (DT) generates real-time digital counterparts of physical devices, enabling instantaneous monitoring and decision-making for remote system operations. This paper presents an online remote tactile texture sharing framework that integrates DT with AI-enhanced haptic rendering. By combining XR-based haptic feedback and a fingertip tactile unit equipped with a surface morphological probe, we establish an online texture twinning system that synergizes physical metrology with deep learning to enhance the spatial resolution of tactile probes. Experimental validation on eight types of materials — including metals, polymers, and composites — demonstrates that our lightweight convolutional neural network achieves real-time texture reconstruction with a mean absolute error (MAE) of 2.13 mV and a root mean square error (RMSE) of 2.60 mV, showing high consistency between predicted and actual surface roughness. These results highlight the framework’s potential in advancing remote collaboration and immersive experiences within the emerging Tactile Internet paradigm.
ER  - 

