AB  - The Hybrid Tactile Internet Framework revolutionizes real-time human-machine interactions by integrating edge computing, cloud resources, and multi-modal technologies for ultra-low latency communication and precise synchronization. The framework leverages advanced AI models, including Transformer architectures and ResNet variants, for accurate data processing and hybrid reinforcement learning for real-time decision-making. It achieved an average synchronization accuracy of 99.85%, end-to-end latency as low as 0.95ms under 5G URLLC, and a multi-modal feedback success rate of 98.90% across diverse scenarios. Resource allocation remained efficient, with peak energy efficiency of 91.2% under low load conditions and 78.1% at peak load. Haptic systems demonstrated exceptional performance with feedback accuracy of 98.8% and response times under 1ms, Real-world evaluations in virtual surgery, remote robotics, and VR gaming highlighted a decision-making success rate of 98.5%-99.1%, with user satisfaction scores averaging 4.8/5. The proposed framework offers significant potential for applications in telemedicine, collaborative robotics, and immersive VR, paving the way for seamless, scalable, and reliable tactile internet systems.
ER  - 

