AB  - We address cooperative work where an object is carried collaboratively by two remote robot systems with force feedback in this paper. In the work, two users manipulate two haptic interface devices to control a robot together (called dual-user operation here) in coordination with another robot that moves automatically. We enhance robot position control by taking account of network delays in the dual-user operation to diminish the force exerted on the object. Experimental results confirm the effectiveness of our enhanced control.
