AB  - Industry 4.0 enabled Augmented reality (AR) is a better representation of the real world made possible by using cutting-edge visual, aural, or other tangibly improved elements communicated through innovation. In order to increase insight, AR entails superimposing visual, audible, or other tactile data over the real world. Expanded reality can be used by businesses and retailers to promote goods or services, launch innovative marketing campaigns, and compile novel customer data. This manuscript centralizes the importance of AR in education in generating interest, learning climate, content clarity, cooperation, memory, tactile turn of events, and cost-viability. It provides the history of AR in education and AR applications like human anatomy atlas 2021, holo-human, VR frog dissection, touch surgery, 4D interactive anatomy, visible body and plantale. This manuscript also highlights the challenges of Industry 4.0 enabled AR, as an absence of fundamental preparation, contingent upon the equipment, content movability issues, and expense of planning these intuitive stages and advanced education is still in its early stages. This study provides future solutions for Industry 4.0 enabled AR. It gives the analysis of traditional and Industry 4.0 enabled AR.
ER  - 

